                            <comment id="17818551" author="tilman" created="Mon, 19 Feb 2024 17:57:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I can&apos;t access that DSS issue without registering, which I don&apos;t want to. In the file there, does the /P entry of the widget point to the page? If yes, then all I&apos;d have to do is to make the change like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (signatureField == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
        {
            .....
        }
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
        {
            firstWidget = signatureField.getWidgets().get(0);
            sigObject.getCOSObject().setNeedToBeUpdated(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (firstWidget.getPage() != &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;)
            {
                page = firstWidget.getPage();
            }
        }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17818582" author="mkl" created="Mon, 19 Feb 2024 22:14:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In the case at hand, &lt;b&gt;P&lt;/b&gt; does point to the page. Nonetheless, it&apos;s the case of a PDF prepared by a third party, i.e. something the eSig DSS / PDFBox user cannot control and that can change any time. Thus, a solution not requiring &lt;b&gt;P&lt;/b&gt; to point back to the page in question, would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;On the other hand, if we assume an existing signature field annotation to already be properly referenced from the page it is on, we don&apos;t need a page object at all. Thus, instead of adding the &lt;tt&gt;if&lt;/tt&gt; block as you proposed, you can simply add &lt;tt&gt;page = null;&lt;/tt&gt; and at the end of the method enclose &lt;tt&gt;List&amp;lt;PDAnnotation&amp;gt; annotations = page.getAnnotations();&lt;/tt&gt; ... &lt;tt&gt;page.getCOSObject().setNeedToBeUpdated(true);&lt;/tt&gt; in a &lt;tt&gt;if (page != null) {...&lt;/tt&gt;} block.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17818700" author="tilman" created="Tue, 20 Feb 2024 08:28:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks, that makes sense, widget, annotation list and page don&apos;t have to be updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
